1. Laser Sweeper1.1. Sweeper Data Acquisition1.1.1. Data Flow1.1.2. Sweeper new and old version entrance1.1.3. Initialize Cloud Configuration1.1.4. Update Cloud Configuration1.1.5. Register or Close the Real-time Data Channel (Return File Relative Path)1.1.6. Register or Close the Real-time Data Channel (Return Byte Array)1.1.7. Get Full File Url1.1.8. Get Data Content of Cloud Storage1.1.9. Get Current Cleaning Data1.1.10. Get History Sweep Records1.1.11. Delete History Sweep Records1.1.12. Clear History Sweep Rcords1.1.13. Get Historical Sweep Records (multi-maps)1.1.14. Clear History Sweep Records (multiple maps)1. Laser Sweeper

Laser sweeper data is divided into real-time data and historical record data. Both types of data include map data and route data, which are stored on the OSS server in the form of files.
The maps and paths of real-time data are stored in different files, and the maps and paths of historical data are stored in the same file. The map and path data are split and read according to the specified rules.
It is recommended that all interfaces be called after the success of initCloudConfig, and the validity period of the configuration information will be updated within half an hour afterupdateCloudConfig

